ndering if the dynamic agent can follow the subprocess, but it didn't seem to work last time. It shows attempts as none for all four operations, so that’s not an option. I’m considering if I could adjust Gradle to let the Graal dynamic agent work with subprocess, but that seems like a dead end too. Maybe I could explore using `ModuleLayer.boot().findModule`, but I'm not sure about that either.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating class order**\\n\\nI'm analyzing the class order for systemAccessorCreation, which uses the already initialized NexusAccessor with a fallback. I need to check the order of subsequent classes. I’m thinking of setting security as @Order(1), system as @Order(2), childFirst as @Order(3), and named as @Order(4). Right now, system is @Order(1), so I need to swap it. I'm concerned about test coverage if ClassInjector is already initialized by previous tests, as it could affect subsequent ones.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering Gradle order**\\n\\nI'm reflecting on how to manage the order in Gradle. It seems like ordering by classpath instead of alphabetically might be the way to go. However, I think I should double-check that approach because the order could make a difference in how things work. It's important for me to ensure I'm managing it correctly, so I'll consider making the necessary edits and adjustments accordingly. Let's see how that plays out!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_DjTDavVHr1Oopt7qTGr9g9UK|fc_07066c0709a9ed1a0169faaea1ded48190b76ffbe57b4a3cf0", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.projectreactor.tools/blockhound/1.0.8.RELEASE/src/test/java/io_projectreactor_tools/blockhound/NexusAccessorInnerDispatcherInnerCreationActionTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "    @Test\n    @Order(1)\n    void systemAccessorCreationInjectsNexusAndResolvesItsPublicMethods() {\n        try {\n            assertThat(NexusAccessor.isAlive()).isTrue();\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            verifyNativeImageUnsupportedFeature(error);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    @Order(2)\n    void childFirstAccessorWithoutResourcesFallsBackToSystemNexus() throws Exception {\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    @Order(1)\n    @SuppressWarnings(\"removal\")\n    void creationActionFallsBackToSystemNexusWhenReflectiveInjectionIsDenied() throws Exception {\n        SecurityManager previousSecurityManager = null;\n        boolean securityManagerChanged = false;\n        Object dispatcher;\n        try {\n            previousSecurityManager = System.getSecurityManager();\n            System.setSecurityManager(new DenyingAccessibleObjectSecurityManager());\n            securityManagerChanged = true;\n\n            dispatcher = ExposedNexusAccessor.creationAction().run();\n        } catch (UnsupportedOperationException exception) {\n            assertThat(exception).isNotNull();\n            return;\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            verifyNativeImageUnsupportedFeature(error);\n            return;\n        } finally {\n            if (securityManagerChanged) {\n                System.setSecurityManager(previousSecurityManager);\n            }\n        }\n\n        assertThat(ExposedNexusAccessor.isDispatcherAlive(dispatcher)).isTrue();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    @Order(2)\n    void systemAccessorCreationInjectsNexusAndResolvesItsPublicMethods() {\n        try {\n            assertThat(NexusAccessor.isAlive()).isTrue();\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            verifyNativeImageUnsupportedFeature(error);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    @Order(3)\n    void childFirstAccessorWithoutResourcesFallsBackToSystemNexus() throws Exception {\n"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    @Order(3)\n    @SuppressWarnings(\"removal\")\n    void creationActionFallsBackToSystemNexusWhenReflectiveInjectionIsDenied() throws Exception {\n        SecurityManager previousSecurityManager = null;\n        boolean securityManagerChanged = false;\n        Object dispatcher;\n        try {\